<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 2em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">The other domain has temporary networking problems.</li>
</ul>
<div style="margin: 1em 0px; padding: 8px 0px 8px 54px; border-width: 1px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-bottom-style: solid; border-top-color: #eeeeee; border-bottom-color: #eeeeee; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; min-height: 30px; background-image: url('https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/'); background-repeat: no-repeat;">If you got this error message when sending to someone in your organization or company (within the same Google Apps domain), you might need to&nbsp;<a style="color: #7759ae; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none;" href="https://support.google.com/a/answer/33352" target="_blank">configure your MX records</a>.</div>
